Problem: Loading 100K+ row files causes memory spikes and slow initial renders

CRITICAL: This is foundational infrastructure required by Task 81 (Virtual Scrolling) and essential for handling large datasets without performance degradation.

Solution: Progressive loading in chunks

File: app/services/shared/progressive-loader.server.ts

```typescript
export class ProgressiveDataLoader {
  private CHUNK_SIZE = 10000; // 10K rows per chunk

  async *loadFileInChunks(fileId: string): AsyncGenerator<any[]> {
    const totalRows = await this.getRowCount(fileId);
    const chunks = Math.ceil(totalRows / this.CHUNK_SIZE);

    for (let i = 0; i < chunks; i++) {
      const offset = i * this.CHUNK_SIZE;
      const query = `SELECT * FROM '${fileId}' LIMIT ${this.CHUNK_SIZE} OFFSET ${offset}`;
      const chunk = await duckdb.query(query);
      yield chunk;
    }
  }

  async getRowCount(fileId: string): Promise<number> {
    const result = await duckdb.query(`SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM '${fileId}'`);
    return result[0].count;
  }
}
```

Integration:
- FileUploadService uses progressive loading
- Virtual scrolling receives chunks incrementally
- Loading indicators show progress
